# Fix `@` file references with spaces/special characters

## Context

When a user selects a file via the `@` file picker and the filename contains spaces or special characters (e.g. `my file.png`, `image (1).png`), the file content is never sent to the AI. The path is inserted correctly into the input (`@src/my file.png`), but the extraction regex `/@([^\s@]+)/g` stops at the first space, capturing only `src/my` instead of the full path. The file lookup then fails silently.

## Root Cause

Two regexes use `[^\s@]` which breaks on whitespace:
- **`src/image-utils.ts:19`** — `/@([^\s@]+)/g` (extraction — the main bug)
- **`src/components/PromptInput.tsx:58`** — `/@([^\s@]*)$/` (autocomplete detection — secondary)

## Solution: Quote wrapping

Paths with special chars get wrapped in double quotes at insertion: `@"src/my file.png"`. Regexes are updated to handle both `@"quoted path"` and `@unquoted-path`.

## Changes

### 1. `src/image-utils.ts` — Update extraction regex and callback

**Line 19** — new regex with alternation (quoted first, then unquoted):
```
/@"([^"]+)"|@([^\s@]+)/g
```

**Lines 27–33** — callback now handles two capture groups:
```typescript
.replace(FILE_REF_RE, (match, quotedPath: string | undefined, unquotedPath: string | undefined) => {
  const path = quotedPath ?? unquotedPath!;
  if (isImageExtension(path)) {
    imagePaths.push(path);
    return '';
  }
  return match;
})
```

### 2. `src/components/PromptInput.tsx` — Two changes

**Lines 56–66** — Detection regex: try quoted form first, fall back to unquoted:
```typescript
const atMatch = useMemo(() => {
  const quotedMatch = value.match(/@"([^"@]*)$/);
  if (quotedMatch) {
    return {
      query: quotedMatch[1] || '',
      startIndex: value.length - quotedMatch[0].length,
    };
  }
  const match = value.match(/@([^\s@]*)$/);
  if (match) {
    return {
      query: match[1] || '',
      startIndex: value.length - match[0].length,
    };
  }
  return null;
},
